      "content": {
        "title": "Craniocervical Junction Disorders — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Congenital and acquired disorders of the occiput-C2 region including basilar invagination, odontoid pathology, and rheumatoid instability.",
        "summary": "Rheumatoid pannus causes atlantoaxial instability. Odontoid fractures in elderly may be managed operatively or with C1-C2 fusion."
      },
